Subject: Poincare Symbolic Ricci Flow Model Boundary

Description: Project-local tool for deciding whether "symbolic Ricci flow" is metaphor, computational-cognition model, formal transform, or overclaim.

& [PoincareSymbolicRicciFlowModelBoundary] is a math inquiry tool
  + [tool_uuid] is 70f97703-c0fc-4d15-9b01-53a657fb7478
  + [problem] is Poincare Conjecture
  + [created_at] is 2026-06-26
  + [trigger_record] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\events\proof_inquiry\2026-06-26_poincare_solved_problem_authority_gate_001.sop
  + [role] is specify what symbolic Ricci flow would need in order to become a model independent from the solved Poincare proof
  + [not_role] is replacing Ricci flow with cognition, proving Poincare, or using model analogy as evidence for other Millennium solutions

& [ModelRequirementSet] is the minimum model boundary
  + [requirement_001_state_space] is define the objects being smoothed, such as concepts, embeddings, graph nodes, documents, or typed assertions
  + [requirement_002_geometry_or_adjacency] is define a metric, graph, topology, similarity relation, or curvature proxy
  + [requirement_003_update_rule] is define an iteration rule that changes the state by reducing a measured irregularity
  + [requirement_004_invariant] is define what must be preserved under smoothing
  + [requirement_005_convergence_measure] is define coherence, entropy, curvature, inconsistency, or loss metric and its target behavior
  + [requirement_006_failure_modes] is define collapse, over-smoothing, loss of distinction, or false coherence
  + [requirement_007_validation] is define experiment, theorem, or observation that can support the model
  + [requirement_008_authority_boundary] is state that model success is not Poincare proof and not evidence for unsolved Millennium problems

& [ClassificationRules] is the boundary logic
  + [rule_001] is if only smoothing language is present, classify as metaphor
  + [rule_002] is if state space, update rule, and convergence metric are supplied, classify as computational-model candidate
  + [rule_003] is if formal objects and theorems are supplied, classify as formal-transform candidate
  + [rule_004] is if it claims to prove Poincare or P vs NP by analogy, classify as overclaim

(poincare_symbolic_ricci_flow_model_boundary) :symbolic_ricci_flow_claim: /state, geometry, update, invariant, convergence, validation/ |proof-analogy|
  + [inside] is cognitive/model boundary and validation requirements
  + [boundary] is model meaning can be valuable while remaining outside topology proof
  |outside| analogy as theorem, smoothing as proof, and symbolic collapse as solution transfer
